Package com.jalios.jcmsplugin.collaborativespace.builder

Class CSBuilder

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.jalios.jcmsplugin.collaborativespace.builder.CSBuilder
  • public class CSBuilder
extends java.lang.Object
    A Builder pattern class to build CollaborativeSpace for unit test and/or load tests,...
    To use a simpliest form, see build().
    To have full control, see buildAsIs().
    For some tests, CSRequest type must be correctly set up in CS Request workspace. See CSBuilderUtil.initCSRequestWorkflow()
    Since:
    csp-7.0
    Author:
    Sylvain DEVAUX <sylvain.devaux@jalios.com>

      • build

        public generated.CollaborativeSpace build()
        Build a CollaborativeSpace with minimal informations.
        Missing informations will be set to a default value if possible. Those are:
        • title (in cs's mainLanguage)
        • author
        • description
        • model
        • language
        • accessPolicy

        Simpliest form: 

         CollaborativeSpace cs = new CSBuilder().build();

        Customize the builder: 

         CSBuilder csBuilder = new CSBuilder();
 csBuilder.description("my description"); // Customizing the description field
 CollaborativeSpace cs = csBuilder.build();

        When creation succeeds, the caller must manage CS deletion. 

         Set<Data> initialDataSet = channel.getAllDataSet();
 CollaborativeSpace cs = new CSBuilder().build();
 deleteOnTearDown(cs.getWorkspace(), initialDataSet);
        Returns:
        CollaborativeSpace

      • buildAsIs
